        <h1 style="font-size: 3.5rem; color: var(--navy); margin-bottom: 2rem;">Privacy Policy</h1>
        
        <div class="legal-content">
            <p><strong>Last Updated: April 2026</strong></p>
            <p>First Home Renovations ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share information when you use our website to find home improvement contractors.</p>

            <h3>1. Information Collection</h3>
            <p>When you request a renovation estimate, we collect personal details including:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Full name and contact information (email, mailing address).</li>
                <li>Property details (type of home, year built, specific rooms needing renovation).</li>
                <li>Project preferences (budget range, desired materials, timeline).</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2. How We Use Lead Data</h3>
            <p>Your information is used specifically to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Identify the best-suited kitchen, bathroom, or full-home remodeling contractors in our network.</li>
                <li>Transfer your project details to selected contractors so they can prepare accurate estimates.</li>
                <li>Send you follow-up emails regarding your project status.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>3. Data Sharing with Contractors</h3>
            <p>By submitting a request, you acknowledge that your data will be shared with independent businesses within our referral network. These businesses are independent of First Home Renovations and have their own privacy practices.</p>

            <h3>4. Security of Property Data</h3>
            <p>We take property security seriously. Information about your home's layout or structural needs is shared only with vetted contractors for the purpose of professional evaluation.</p>

            <h3>5. Marketing Communications</h3>
            <p>We may send periodic newsletters about home design trends and maintenance tips. You can opt-out at any time via the link in our emails.</p>
